824  struct DefaultEventFormatter : public EventFormatter {
825 
826  virtual std::string format(const UnexpectedMethodCallEvent &e) override {
827  std::ostringstream out;
828  out << "Unexpected method invocation: ";
829  out << e.getInvocation().format() << std::endl;
830  if (UnexpectedType::Unmatched == e.getUnexpectedType()) {
831  out << " Could not find Any recorded behavior to support this method call.";
832  } else {
833  out << " An unmocked method was invoked. All used virtual methods must be stubbed!";
834  }
835  return out.str();
836  }
837 
838 
839  virtual std::string format(const SequenceVerificationEvent &e) override {
840  std::ostringstream out;
841  out << "Verification error" << std::endl;
842 
843  out << "Expected pattern: ";
844  const std::vector<fakeit::Sequence *> expectedPattern = e.expectedPattern();
845  out << formatExpectedPattern(expectedPattern) << std::endl;
846 
847  out << "Expected matches: ";
848  formatExpectedCount(out, e.verificationType(), e.expectedCount());
849  out << std::endl;
850 
851  out << "Actual matches : " << e.actualCount() << std::endl;
852 
853  auto actualSequence = e.actualSequence();
854  out << "Actual sequence : total of " << actualSequence.size() << " actual invocations";
855  if (actualSequence.size() == 0) {
856  out << ".";
857  } else {
858  out << ":" << std::endl;
859  }
860  formatInvocationList(out, actualSequence);
861 
862  return out.str();
863  }
864 
865  virtual std::string format(const NoMoreInvocationsVerificationEvent &e) override {
866  std::ostringstream out;
867  out << "Verification error" << std::endl;
868  out << "Expected no more invocations!! But the following unverified invocations were found:" << std::endl;
869  formatInvocationList(out, e.unverifedIvocations());
870  return out.str();
871  }
872 
873  private:
874 
875  static std::string formatSequence(const Sequence &val) {
876  const ConcatenatedSequence *cs = dynamic_cast<const ConcatenatedSequence *>(&val);
877  if (cs) {
878  return format(*cs);
879  }
880  const RepeatedSequence *rs = dynamic_cast<const RepeatedSequence *>(&val);
881  if (rs) {
882  return format(*rs);
883  }
884 
885 
886  std::vector<Invocation::Matcher *> vec;
887  val.getExpectedSequence(vec);
888  return vec[0]->format();
889  }
890 
891  static void formatExpectedCount(std::ostream &out, fakeit::VerificationType verificationType,
892  int expectedCount) {
893  if (verificationType == fakeit::VerificationType::Exact)
894  out << "exactly ";
895 
896  if (verificationType == fakeit::VerificationType::AtLeast)
897  out << "at least ";
898 
899  out << expectedCount;
900  }
901 
902  static void formatInvocationList(std::ostream &out, const std::vector<fakeit::Invocation *> &actualSequence) {
903  size_t max_size = actualSequence.size();
904  if (max_size > 5)
905  max_size = 5;
906 
907  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < max_size; i++) {
908  out << " ";
909  auto invocation = actualSequence[i];
910  out << invocation->format();
911  if (i < max_size - 1)
912  out << std::endl;
913  }
914 
915  if (actualSequence.size() > max_size)
916  out << std::endl << " ...";
917  }
918 
919  static std::string format(const ConcatenatedSequence &val) {
920  std::ostringstream out;
921  out << formatSequence(val.getLeft()) << " + " << formatSequence(val.getRight());
922  return out.str();
923  }
924 
925  static std::string format(const RepeatedSequence &val) {
926  std::ostringstream out;
927  const ConcatenatedSequence *cs = dynamic_cast<const ConcatenatedSequence *>(&val.getSequence());
928  const RepeatedSequence *rs = dynamic_cast<const RepeatedSequence *>(&val.getSequence());
929  if (rs || cs)
930  out << '(';
931  out << formatSequence(val.getSequence());
932  if (rs || cs)
933  out << ')';
934 
935  out << " * " << val.getTimes();
936  return out.str();
937  }
938 
939  static std::string formatExpectedPattern(const std::vector<fakeit::Sequence *> &expectedPattern) {
940  std::string expectedPatternStr;
941  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < expectedPattern.size(); i++) {
942  Sequence *s = expectedPattern[i];
943  expectedPatternStr += formatSequence(*s);
944  if (i < expectedPattern.size() - 1)
945  expectedPatternStr += " ... ";
946  }
947  return expectedPatternStr;
948  }
949  };
950 }

5313  template<typename BaseType>
5314  void addBaseClass() {
5315  static_assert(std::is_base_of<BaseType, C>::value, "C must be a derived class of BaseType");
5316  RTTIBaseClassDescriptor *desc = new RTTIBaseClassDescriptor();
5317  desc->pTypeDescriptor = &typeid(BaseType);
5318  pBaseClassArray[numBaseClasses] = desc;
5319  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < numBaseClasses; i++) {
5320  pBaseClassArray[i]->numContainedBases++;
5321  }
5322  numBaseClasses++;
5323  }

5326  void addBaseClass() {
5327  static_assert(std::is_base_of<B1, head>::value, "invalid inheritance list");
5328  addBaseClass<head>();
5329  addBaseClass<B1, tail...>();
5330  }

6087  I != std::tuple_size<typename std::remove_reference<TupleType>::type>::value>::type>
6088  static void for_each(TupleType &&t, FunctionType &f, std::integral_constant<size_t, I>) {

6706  class RecordedMethodBody : public MethodInvocationHandler<R, arglist...>, public ActualInvocationsSource, public ActualInvocationsContainer {

6708  struct MatchedInvocationHandler : ActualInvocationHandler<R, arglist...> {
6709 
6710  virtual ~MatchedInvocationHandler() = default;
6711 
6712  MatchedInvocationHandler(typename ActualInvocation<arglist...>::Matcher *matcher,
6713  ActualInvocationHandler<R, arglist...> *invocationHandler) :
6714  _matcher{matcher}, _invocationHandler{invocationHandler} {
6715  }
6716 
6717  virtual R handleMethodInvocation(ArgumentsTuple<arglist...> & args) override
6718  {
6719  Destructible &destructable = *_invocationHandler;
6720  ActualInvocationHandler<R, arglist...> &invocationHandler = dynamic_cast<ActualInvocationHandler<R, arglist...> &>(destructable);
6721  return invocationHandler.handleMethodInvocation(args);
6722  }
6723 
6724  typename ActualInvocation<arglist...>::Matcher &getMatcher() const {
6725  Destructible &destructable = *_matcher;
6726  typename ActualInvocation<arglist...>::Matcher &matcher = dynamic_cast<typename ActualInvocation<arglist...>::Matcher &>(destructable);
6727  return matcher;
6728  }
6729 
6730  private:
6731  std::shared_ptr<Destructible> _matcher;
6732  std::shared_ptr<Destructible> _invocationHandler;
6733  };
6734 
6735 
6736  FakeitContext &_fakeit;
6737  MethodInfo _method;
6738 
6739  std::vector<std::shared_ptr<Destructible>> _invocationHandlers;
6740  std::vector<std::shared_ptr<Destructible>> _actualInvocations;
6741 
6742  MatchedInvocationHandler *buildMatchedInvocationHandler(
6743  typename ActualInvocation<arglist...>::Matcher *invocationMatcher,
6744  ActualInvocationHandler<R, arglist...> *invocationHandler) {
6745  return new MatchedInvocationHandler(invocationMatcher, invocationHandler);
6746  }
6747 
6748  MatchedInvocationHandler *getInvocationHandlerForActualArgs(ActualInvocation<arglist...> &invocation) {
6749  for (auto i = _invocationHandlers.rbegin(); i != _invocationHandlers.rend(); ++i) {
6750  std::shared_ptr<Destructible> curr = *i;
6751  Destructible &destructable = *curr;
6752  MatchedInvocationHandler &im = asMatchedInvocationHandler(destructable);
6753  if (im.getMatcher().matches(invocation)) {
6754  return &im;
6755  }
6756  }
6757  return nullptr;
6758  }
6759 
6760  MatchedInvocationHandler &asMatchedInvocationHandler(Destructible &destructable) {
6761  MatchedInvocationHandler &im = dynamic_cast<MatchedInvocationHandler &>(destructable);
6762  return im;
6763  }
6764 
6765  ActualInvocation<arglist...> &asActualInvocation(Destructible &destructable) const {
6766  ActualInvocation<arglist...> &invocation = dynamic_cast<ActualInvocation<arglist...> &>(destructable);
6767  return invocation;
6768  }
6769 
6770  public:
6771 
6772  RecordedMethodBody(FakeitContext &fakeit, std::string name) :
6773  _fakeit(fakeit), _method{MethodInfo::nextMethodOrdinal(), name} { }
6774

6776  }

6780  }

6787  void addMethodInvocationHandler(typename ActualInvocation<arglist...>::Matcher *matcher,
6788  ActualInvocationHandler<R, arglist...> *invocationHandler) {
6789  ActualInvocationHandler<R, arglist...> *mock = buildMatchedInvocationHandler(matcher, invocationHandler);
6790  std::shared_ptr<Destructible> destructable{mock};
6791  _invocationHandlers.push_back(destructable);
6792  }
6793 
6794  void reset() {
6795  _invocationHandlers.clear();
6796  _actualInvocations.clear();
6797  }
6798 
6799  void clear() override {
6800  _actualInvocations.clear();
6801  }
6802 
6803  R handleMethodInvocation(const typename fakeit::production_arg<arglist>::type... args) override {
6804  unsigned int ordinal = Invocation::nextInvocationOrdinal();
6805  MethodInfo &method = this->getMethod();
6806  auto actualInvocation = new ActualInvocation<arglist...>(ordinal, method, std::forward<const typename fakeit::production_arg<arglist>::type>(args)...);
6807 
6808 
6809  std::shared_ptr<Destructible> actualInvocationDtor{actualInvocation};
6810 
6811  auto invocationHandler = getInvocationHandlerForActualArgs(*actualInvocation);
6812  if (invocationHandler) {
6813  auto &matcher = invocationHandler->getMatcher();
6814  actualInvocation->setActualMatcher(&matcher);
6815  _actualInvocations.push_back(actualInvocationDtor);
6816  try {
6817  return invocationHandler->handleMethodInvocation(actualInvocation->getActualArguments());
6818  } catch (NoMoreRecordedActionException &) {
6819  }
6820  }
6821 
6822  UnexpectedMethodCallEvent event(UnexpectedType::Unmatched, *actualInvocation);
6823  _fakeit.handle(event);
6824  std::string format{_fakeit.format(event)};
6825  UnexpectedMethodCallException e(format);
6826  throw e;
6827  }
6828 
6829  void scanActualInvocations(const std::function<void(ActualInvocation<arglist...> &)> &scanner) {
6830  for (auto destructablePtr : _actualInvocations) {
6831  ActualInvocation<arglist...> &invocation = asActualInvocation(*destructablePtr);
6832  scanner(invocation);
6833  }
6834  }
6835 
6836  void getActualInvocations(std::unordered_set<Invocation *> &into) const override {
6837  for (auto destructablePtr : _actualInvocations) {
6838  Invocation &invocation = asActualInvocation(*destructablePtr);
6839  into.insert(&invocation);
6840  }
6841  }

6951  f(func), times(1) {
6952  }

6955  f(func), times(t) {
6956  }

7247  template<typename R, typename ... arglist>
7248  struct ActionSequence : ActualInvocationHandler<R,arglist...> {
7249 
7250  ActionSequence() {
7251  clear();
7252  }
7253 
7254  void AppendDo(Action<R, arglist...> *action) {
7255  append(action);
7256  }
7257 
7258  virtual R handleMethodInvocation(ArgumentsTuple<arglist...> & args) override
7259  {
7260  std::shared_ptr<Destructible> destructablePtr = _recordedActions.front();
7261  Destructible &destructable = *destructablePtr;
7262  Action<R, arglist...> &action = dynamic_cast<Action<R, arglist...> &>(destructable);
7263  std::function<void()> finallyClause = [&]() -> void {
7264  if (action.isDone())
7265  _recordedActions.erase(_recordedActions.begin());
7266  };
7267  Finally onExit(finallyClause);
7268  return action.invoke(args);
7269  }
7270 
7271  private:
7272 
7273  struct NoMoreRecordedAction : Action<R, arglist...> {
7274 
7275 
7276 
7277 
7278 
7279 
7280 
7281  virtual R invoke(const ArgumentsTuple<arglist...> &) override {
7282  throw NoMoreRecordedActionException();
7283  }
7284 
7285  virtual bool isDone() override {
7286  return false;
7287  }
7288  };
7289 
7290  void append(Action<R, arglist...> *action) {
7291  std::shared_ptr<Destructible> destructable{action};
7292  _recordedActions.insert(_recordedActions.end() - 1, destructable);
7293  }
7294 
7295  void clear() {
7296  _recordedActions.clear();
7297  auto actionPtr = std::shared_ptr<Destructible> {new NoMoreRecordedAction()};
7298  _recordedActions.push_back(actionPtr);
7299  }
7300 
7301  std::vector<std::shared_ptr<Destructible>> _recordedActions;
7302  };

7367  template<unsigned int index, typename ... arglist>
7368  class MatchersCollector {

7370  std::vector<Destructible *> &_matchers;
7371 
7372  public:
7373 
7374 
7375  template<std::size_t N>
7376  using ArgType = typename std::tuple_element<N, std::tuple<arglist...>>::type;
7377 
7378  template<std::size_t N>
7379  using NakedArgType = typename naked_type<ArgType<index>>::type;
7380 
7381  template<std::size_t N>
7382  using ArgMatcherCreatorType = decltype(std::declval<TypedMatcherCreator<NakedArgType<N>>>());
7383 
7384  MatchersCollector(std::vector<Destructible *> &matchers)
7385  : _matchers(matchers) {
7386  }
7387 
7388  void CollectMatchers() {
7389  }
7390 
7391  template<typename Head>
7392  typename std::enable_if<
7393  std::is_constructible<NakedArgType<index>, Head>::value, void>
7394  ::type CollectMatchers(const Head &value) {
7395 
7396  TypedMatcher<NakedArgType<index>> *d = Eq<NakedArgType<index>>(value).createMatcher();
7397  _matchers.push_back(d);
7398  }
7399 
7400  template<typename Head, typename ...Tail>
7401  typename std::enable_if<
7402  std::is_constructible<NakedArgType<index>, Head>::value
7403  , void>
7404  ::type CollectMatchers(const Head &head, const Tail &... tail) {
7405  CollectMatchers(head);
7406  MatchersCollector<index + 1, arglist...> c(_matchers);
7407  c.CollectMatchers(tail...);
7408  }
7409 
7410  template<typename Head>
7411  typename std::enable_if<
7412  std::is_base_of<TypedMatcherCreator<NakedArgType<index>>, Head>::value, void>
7413  ::type CollectMatchers(const Head &creator) {
7414  TypedMatcher<NakedArgType<index>> *d = creator.createMatcher();
7415  _matchers.push_back(d);
7416  }
7417 
7418  template<typename Head, typename ...Tail>
7419 
7420  typename std::enable_if<
7421  std::is_base_of<TypedMatcherCreator<NakedArgType<index>>, Head>::value, void>
7422  ::type CollectMatchers(const Head &head, const Tail &... tail) {
7423  CollectMatchers(head);
7424  MatchersCollector<index + 1, arglist...> c(_matchers);
7425  c.CollectMatchers(tail...);
7426  }

7430  std::is_same<AnyMatcher, Head>::value, void>
7431  ::type CollectMatchers(const Head &) {

7433  _matchers.push_back(d);

8016  UnexpectedMethodCallEvent event(UnexpectedType::Unmocked, invocation);
8017  auto &fakeit = getMockImpl(this)->_fakeit;
8018  fakeit.handle(event);
8019 
8020  std::string format = fakeit.format(event);
8021  UnexpectedMethodCallException e(format);
8022  throw e;
8023  }

8049  R (C::*vMethod)(arglist...)) {
8050  if (!proxy.isMethodStubbed(vMethod)) {
8051  proxy.template stubMethod<id>(vMethod, createRecordedMethodBody < R, arglist... > (*this, vMethod));

8055  return *methodMock;

8061  }

8064  return *dtorMock;

8268  }

8271  reference = new RefCount();
8272  reference->AddRef();
8273  }
8274 
8275  smart_ptr(const smart_ptr<T> &sp) : pData(sp.pData), reference(sp.reference) {
8276  reference->AddRef();
8277  }
8278 
8279  ~smart_ptr() THROWS {
8280  if (reference->Release() == 0) {
8281  delete reference;
8282  delete pData;
8283  }
8284  }

8288  }

8291  return pData;
8292  }
8293

8295  if (this != &sp) {
8296 
8297 
8298  if (reference->Release() == 0) {
8299  delete reference;
8300  delete pData;
8301  }
8302 
8303 
8304 
8305  pData = sp.pData;
8306  reference = sp.reference;
8307  reference->AddRef();
8308  }

8310  }

8421  static void sortByInvocationOrder(std::unordered_set<Invocation *> &ivocations,
8422  std::vector<Invocation *> &result) {
8423  auto comparator = [](Invocation *a, Invocation *b) -> bool {
8424  return a->getOrdinal() < b->getOrdinal();
8425  };
8426  std::set<Invocation *, bool (*)(Invocation *a, Invocation *b)> sortedIvocations(comparator);
8427  for (auto i : ivocations)
8428  sortedIvocations.insert(i);
8429 
8430  for (auto i : sortedIvocations)
8431  result.push_back(i);
8432  }

8491 namespace fakeit {
8492  struct MatchAnalysis {
8493  std::vector<Invocation *> actualSequence;
8494  std::vector<Invocation *> matchedInvocations;
8495  int count;
8496 
8497  void run(InvocationsSourceProxy &involvedInvocationSources, std::vector<Sequence *> &expectedPattern) {
8498  getActualInvocationSequence(involvedInvocationSources, actualSequence);
8499  count = countMatches(expectedPattern, actualSequence, matchedInvocations);
8500  }
8501 
8502  private:
8503  static void getActualInvocationSequence(InvocationsSourceProxy &involvedMocks,
8504  std::vector<Invocation *> &actualSequence) {
8505  std::unordered_set<Invocation *> actualInvocations;
8506  collectActualInvocations(involvedMocks, actualInvocations);
8507  InvocationUtils::sortByInvocationOrder(actualInvocations, actualSequence);
8508  }
8509 
8510  static int countMatches(std::vector<Sequence *> &pattern, std::vector<Invocation *> &actualSequence,
8511  std::vector<Invocation *> &matchedInvocations) {
8512  int end = -1;
8513  int count = 0;
8514  int startSearchIndex = 0;
8515  while (findNextMatch(pattern, actualSequence, startSearchIndex, end, matchedInvocations)) {
8516  count++;
8517  startSearchIndex = end;
8518  }
8519  return count;
8520  }
8521 
8522  static void collectActualInvocations(InvocationsSourceProxy &involvedMocks,
8523  std::unordered_set<Invocation *> &actualInvocations) {
8524  involvedMocks.getActualInvocations(actualInvocations);
8525  }
8526 
8527  static bool findNextMatch(std::vector<Sequence *> &pattern, std::vector<Invocation *> &actualSequence,
8528  int startSearchIndex, int &end,
8529  std::vector<Invocation *> &matchedInvocations) {
8530  for (auto sequence : pattern) {
8531  int index = findNextMatch(sequence, actualSequence, startSearchIndex);
8532  if (index == -1) {
8533  return false;
8534  }
8535  collectMatchedInvocations(actualSequence, matchedInvocations, index, sequence->size());
8536  startSearchIndex = index + sequence->size();
8537  }
8538  end = startSearchIndex;
8539  return true;
8540  }
8541 
8542 
8543  static void collectMatchedInvocations(std::vector<Invocation *> &actualSequence,
8544  std::vector<Invocation *> &matchedInvocations, int start,
8545  int length) {
8546  int indexAfterMatchedPattern = start + length;
8547  for (; start < indexAfterMatchedPattern; start++) {
8548  matchedInvocations.push_back(actualSequence[start]);
8549  }
8550  }
8551 
8552 
8553  static bool isMatch(std::vector<Invocation *> &actualSequence,
8554  std::vector<Invocation::Matcher *> &expectedSequence, int start) {
8555  bool found = true;
8556  for (unsigned int j = 0; found && j < expectedSequence.size(); j++) {
8557  Invocation *actual = actualSequence[start + j];
8558  Invocation::Matcher *expected = expectedSequence[j];
8559  found = found && expected->matches(*actual);
8560  }
8561  return found;
8562  }
8563 
8564  static int findNextMatch(Sequence *&pattern, std::vector<Invocation *> &actualSequence, int startSearchIndex) {
8565  std::vector<Invocation::Matcher *> expectedSequence;
8566  pattern->getExpectedSequence(expectedSequence);
8567  for (int i = startSearchIndex; i < ((int) actualSequence.size() - (int) expectedSequence.size() + 1); i++) {
8568  if (isMatch(actualSequence, expectedSequence, i)) {
8569  return i;
8570  }
8571  }
8572  return -1;
8573  }
8574 
8575  };
8576 }

8580  struct SequenceVerificationExpectation {
8581 
8582  friend class SequenceVerificationProgress;
8583 
8584  ~SequenceVerificationExpectation() THROWS {
8585  if (std::uncaught_exception()) {
8586  return;
8587  }
8588  VerifyExpectation(_fakeit);
8589  }
8590 
8591  void setExpectedPattern(std::vector<Sequence *> expectedPattern) {
8592  _expectedPattern = expectedPattern;
8593  }
8594 
8595  void setExpectedCount(const int count) {
8596  _expectedCount = count;
8597  }
8598 
8599  void setFileInfo(const char * file, int line, const char * callingMethod) {
8600  _file = file;
8601  _line = line;
8602  _testMethod = callingMethod;
8603  }
8604 
8605  private:
8606 
8607  VerificationEventHandler &_fakeit;
8608  InvocationsSourceProxy _involvedInvocationSources;
8609  std::vector<Sequence *> _expectedPattern;
8610  int _expectedCount;
8611 
8612  const char * _file;
8613  int _line;
8614  const char * _testMethod;
8615  bool _isVerified;
8616 
8617  SequenceVerificationExpectation(
8618  VerificationEventHandler &fakeit,
8619  InvocationsSourceProxy mocks,
8620  std::vector<Sequence *> &expectedPattern) :
8621  _fakeit(fakeit),
8622  _involvedInvocationSources(mocks),
8623  _expectedPattern(expectedPattern),
8624  _expectedCount(-1),
8625  _line(0),
8626  _isVerified(false) {
8627  }
8628 
8629 
8630  void VerifyExpectation(VerificationEventHandler &verificationErrorHandler) {
8631  if (_isVerified)
8632  return;
8633  _isVerified = true;
8634 
8635  MatchAnalysis ma;
8636  ma.run(_involvedInvocationSources, _expectedPattern);
8637 
8638  if (isAtLeastVerification() && atLeastLimitNotReached(ma.count)) {
8639  return handleAtLeastVerificationEvent(verificationErrorHandler, ma.actualSequence, ma.count);
8640  }
8641 
8642  if (isExactVerification() && exactLimitNotMatched(ma.count)) {
8643  return handleExactVerificationEvent(verificationErrorHandler, ma.actualSequence, ma.count);
8644  }
8645 
8646  markAsVerified(ma.matchedInvocations);
8647  }
8648 
8649  std::vector<Sequence *> &collectSequences(std::vector<Sequence *> &vec) {
8650  return vec;
8651  }
8652 
8653  template<typename ... list>
8654  std::vector<Sequence *> &collectSequences(std::vector<Sequence *> &vec, const Sequence &sequence,
8655  const list &... tail) {
8656  vec.push_back(&const_cast<Sequence &>(sequence));
8657  return collectSequences(vec, tail...);
8658  }
8659 
8660 
8661  static void markAsVerified(std::vector<Invocation *> &matchedInvocations) {
8662  for (auto i : matchedInvocations) {
8663  i->markAsVerified();
8664  }
8665  }
8666 
8667  bool isAtLeastVerification() {
8668 
8669  return _expectedCount < 0;
8670  }
8671 
8672  bool isExactVerification() {
8673  return !isAtLeastVerification();
8674  }
8675 
8676  bool atLeastLimitNotReached(int count) {
8677  return count < -_expectedCount;
8678  }
8679 
8680  bool exactLimitNotMatched(int count) {
8681  return count != _expectedCount;
8682  }
8683 
8684  void handleExactVerificationEvent(VerificationEventHandler &verificationErrorHandler,
8685  std::vector<Invocation *> actualSequence, int count) {
8686  SequenceVerificationEvent evt(VerificationType::Exact, _expectedPattern, actualSequence, _expectedCount,
8687  count);
8688  evt.setFileInfo(_file, _line, _testMethod);
8689  return verificationErrorHandler.handle(evt);
8690  }
8691 
8692  void handleAtLeastVerificationEvent(VerificationEventHandler &verificationErrorHandler,
8693  std::vector<Invocation *> actualSequence, int count) {
8694  SequenceVerificationEvent evt(VerificationType::AtLeast, _expectedPattern, actualSequence, -_expectedCount,
8695  count);
8696  evt.setFileInfo(_file, _line, _testMethod);
8697  return verificationErrorHandler.handle(evt);
8698  }
8699 
8700  };
8701

8759  class Terminator {

8761 
8762  bool toBool() {
8763  try {
8764  ThrowFalseEventHandler eh;
8765  _expectationPtr->VerifyExpectation(eh);
8766  return true;
8767  }
8768  catch (bool e) {
8769  return e;
8770  }
8771  }
8772 
8773  public:
8774  Terminator(smart_ptr<SequenceVerificationExpectation> expectationPtr) : _expectationPtr(expectationPtr) { };
8775 
8776  operator bool() {
8777  return toBool();
8778  }
8779 
8780  bool operator!() const { return !const_cast<Terminator *>(this)->toBool(); }
8781  };

8788  return Terminator(_expectationPtr);
8789  }

8792 
8793  Terminator Never() {
8794  Exactly(0);
8795  return Terminator(_expectationPtr);
8796  }
8797 
8798  Terminator Once() {
8799  Exactly(1);
8800  return Terminator(_expectationPtr);
8801  }
8802 
8803  Terminator Twice() {
8804  Exactly(2);
8805  return Terminator(_expectationPtr);
8806  }

8809  verifyInvocations(-1);
8810  return Terminator(_expectationPtr);
8811  }
8812 
8813  Terminator Exactly(const int times) {
8814  if (times < 0) {
8815  throw std::invalid_argument(std::string("bad argument times:").append(fakeit::to_string(times)));
8816  }
8817  verifyInvocations(times);
8818  return Terminator(_expectationPtr);
8819  }
8820

8822  Exactly(q.quantity);
8823  return Terminator(_expectationPtr);
8824  }
8825 
8826  Terminator AtLeast(const int times) {
8827  if (times < 0) {
8828  throw std::invalid_argument(std::string("bad argument times:").append(fakeit::to_string(times)));
8829  }
8830  verifyInvocations(-times);
8831  return Terminator(_expectationPtr);
8832  }
8833 
8834  Terminator AtLeast(const Quantity &q) {
8835  AtLeast(q.quantity);
8836  return Terminator(_expectationPtr);
8837  }
8838

8980  void VerifyExpectation(VerificationEventHandler &verificationErrorHandler) {
8981  if (_isVerified)
8982  return;
8983  _isVerified = true;
8984 
8985  std::unordered_set<Invocation *> actualInvocations;
8986  InvocationUtils::collectActualInvocations(actualInvocations, _mocks);
8987 
8988  std::unordered_set<Invocation *> nonVerifiedInvocations;
8989  InvocationUtils::selectNonVerifiedInvocations(actualInvocations, nonVerifiedInvocations);
8990 
8991  if (nonVerifiedInvocations.size() > 0) {
8992  std::vector<Invocation *> sortedNonVerifiedInvocations;
8993  InvocationUtils::sortByInvocationOrder(nonVerifiedInvocations, sortedNonVerifiedInvocations);
8994 
8995  std::vector<Invocation *> sortedActualInvocations;
8996  InvocationUtils::sortByInvocationOrder(actualInvocations, sortedActualInvocations);
8997 
8998  NoMoreInvocationsVerificationEvent evt(sortedActualInvocations, sortedNonVerifiedInvocations);
8999  evt.setFileInfo(_file, _line, _callingMethod);
9000  return verificationErrorHandler.handle(evt);
9001  }
9002  }
9003 
9004  };
